 ciao !  
my research interests are in computational complexity
and cryptography,
mainly focusing on interactive proofs, program checking,
zero-knowledge proofs, secret sharing, electronic cash,
pseudo-random functions and generators.
here are some recent papers:




a. de santis, g. di crescenzo, g. persiano, and m. yung,
 on monotone formula closure of statistical zero-knowledge,

focs 94.




a. de santis, g. di crescenzo, and g. persiano,
 the knowledge complexity of quadratic residuosity languages,

theoretical computer science, vol. 132, (1994), pag. 291--317.




g. di crescenzo,  recycling random bits in composed perfect
zero-knowledge,  eurocrypt 95.




a. de santis, g. di crescenzo, and g. persiano, 
zero-knowledge arguments and public key
cryptography, 
information and computation, vol. 121, n. 1, (1995),  pag. 23--40. 




c. blundo, a. de santis, g. di crescenzo, a. giorgio gaggia 
and u. vaccaro,  multi-secret sharing schemes,  crypto 94.





a. de santis, g. di crescenzo, and g. persiano, 
secret sharing and perfect zero-knowledge, 
crypto 93. 








